Set up your Django project using django-admin startproject.
Create an app within your project using python manage.py startapp.
Define models for your app in the models.py file.
Define URLs for your app in the urls.py file.
Create views to handle requests and render templates.
Create templates to display HTML content.
Configure Django settings for your project.
Run database migrations using python manage.py migrate.
Register your models in the admin interface.
Implement user authentication and authorization if needed.
Test your app to ensure everything works as expected.
Deploy your Django project to a web server if needed.
Monitor and maintain your Django project over time.
